# Agent Rules — XAC Base
# This is the shared base for all XAC-consuming projects.
# Layer project-specific rules from _XAC_Config_<ProjectName>/cursor/cursorrules.project.

## 1. Execution

- **Environment:** Windows + PowerShell.
- **Flow:** One copy-paste command block per turn. No multitasking.
- **Editing:** Patch-based edits only. No whole-file overwrites. Use diff/patch or small targeted scripts.
- **Fail-fast:** If a command fails, stop. Provide one diagnostic/fix command. Do not continue on red.

## 2. Git Discipline

**Commits -> GitHub. Pushes -> GCP.**

- **Commits:** Only when the user explicitly asks to commit (e.g. "commit all", "commit to GitHub", "commit these changes").
- **Pushes:** Only when the user explicitly asks to push or deploy (e.g. "push to origin", "push staging", "deploy staging", "merge with staging and deploy"). Pushing triggers deployment to GCP.
- **Other git commands** (`git status`, `git diff`, `git pull`, `git merge`, etc.): only when the user explicitly requests git operations or as part of an approved commit/push/deploy workflow.
- **Deploy workflow:** When the user says "merge with staging and deploy" (or equivalent), follow `.cursor/rules/merge_staging_and_deploy.md`.

## 3. Post-Task Workflow — After Any Code Change

1. `ruff check --fix .` and `ruff format .`
2. Create/update tests per `repo_docs/testing/ENTERPRISE_TESTING_STANDARD.md`
3. Run tests: `pytest modules/<name>/tests/` or `pytest integration_tests/<subpath>` (with servers if needed)
4. `python -m compileall` (relevant paths)
5. **Before push:** run `.\local_ci.ps1`
6. Report completion. **Do not commit unless the user asks to commit; do not push or deploy unless the user asks to push/deploy.**

## 4. Testing

- **Module tests:** `modules/<name>/tests/`
- **Cross-module / E2E:** `integration_tests/`
- **What to mock:** Only external boundaries (Firestore, GCS, third-party APIs). Do not mock our own services/controllers.
- **Run:** `pytest modules/<name>/tests/` or `pytest integration_tests/` from repo root with correct `PYTHONPATH`.
- **Server tests:** Use `.\repo_tooling\restart_servers.ps1` — Start: `-StartOnly`, Stop: `-StopOnly`, Restart: no args.

## 5. GCP Project Lock

All GCP operations use the project defined in `.cursor/rules/project_lock.mdc`. Never deploy, build, or configure resources in any other project.

## 6. Test-Running Agents — Report Only, Do Not Fix

- Run tests and collect failures.
- Add tasks to `.cursor/PROJECT_TASKS.md` with status `pending`, error details, test names.
- **Never** fix errors automatically unless the user explicitly says "fix this" or "resolve this".

## 7. Do Not

- Rename/move many files for "cleanliness"
- Introduce new frameworks without explicit request
- Change output schemas silently
- Bypass smoke/regression
- Propose manual edits (all edits via command line)
- Overwrite whole files for small changes
